description.p:
An embodiment of the present invention discloses a method for advertising border connection information of autonomous system. The method includes:
establishing and maintaining, by a border node of the autonomous system, the border connection information of the autonomous system, the border node of the autonomous system supporting Intermediate System to Intermediate System (ISIS) protocol, wherein the border connection information comprises an identifier of a neighbor border node of a neighbor autonomous system Router_ID) and a number of the neighbor autonomous system (AS Number);
flooding, by the border node of the autonomous system, the border connection information within the autonomous system; and
receiving, by nodes of the autonomous system, the border connection information,
wherein the process of flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises:
including the border connection information in a border connection description Sub-TLV field;
including the border connection description Sub-TLV field in a TLV field;
including the TLV field in a Link State Protocol Data Unit (LSP) message; and
flooding the LSP message.

An embodiment of the present invention discloses an apparatus for advertising border connection information of autonomous system. The apparatus includes:
a border connection information collecting module, configured to obtain border connection information established by the border node, wherein the border connection information comprises an identifier of a neighbor border node of a neighbor autonomous system (Router_ID) and a number of the neighbor autonomous system (AS Number);
a border connection information database, configured to store the border connection information of the autonomous system, the border connection information of the autonomous system including the border connection information established by the border node;
a message generating module, configured to package the border connection information established by the border node into a message; and
a message advertising module, configured to internally flood the message generated in the message generating module within the autonomous system,
wherein the border connection information is included in a border connection description Sub-TLV field, the border connection description Sub-TLV field being included in a TLV field in a Link State Protocol Data Unit (LSP) message if the border node of the autonomous system supports Intermediate System to Intermediate System (ISIS) protocol;
or
wherein the border connection information is included in a Link TLV field, the Link TLV field being included in a Link State Advertisement (LSA) message if the border node of the autonomous system supports Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) protocol.

The border node mainly includes:
a border connection information collecting module, configured to obtain border connection information established by the border node;
a border connection information database, configured to store the border connection information of the autonomous system, which comprises the border connection information established by the border node;
a message generating module, configured to package the border connection information established by the border node into a message; and
a message advertising module, configured to internally flood the message formed in the message generating module within the autonomous system.

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren zum Ankündigen von Grenzverbindungsinformationen eines autonomen Systems, das Folgendes umfasst:
Aufbauen und Aufrechterhalten (101) durch einen Grenzknoten des autonomen Systems von Grenzverbindungsinformationen des autonomen Systems, wobei der Grenzknoten des autonomen Systems ein Zwischensystem-zu-Zwischensystem-Protokoll, ISIS-Protokoll unterstützt, wobei die Grenzverbindungsinformationen einen Identifizierer eines benachbarten Grenzknoten eines benachbarten autonomen Systems, Router_ID, und eine Nummer des benachbarten autonomen Systems, AS-Nummer, enthalten;
Fluten (102) durch den Grenzknoten des autonomen Systems der Grenzverbindungsinformationen in dem autonomen System; und
Empfangen (103) durch einen Knoten des autonomen Systems der Grenzverbindungsinformationen,
wobei der Prozess des Flutens der Grenzverbindungsinformationen in dem autonomen System Folgendes umfasst:
Aufnehmen der Grenzverbindungsinformationen in ein Grenzverbindungsbeschreibungs-Sub-TLV-Feld;
Aufnehmen des Grenzverbindungsbeschreibungs-Sub-TLV-Feldes in ein TLV-Feld;
Aufnehmen des TLV-Feldes in eine Verbindungsstreckenzustandsprotokoll-Dateneinheit-Nachricht, LSP-Nachricht; und
Fluten der LSP-Nachricht.

A method for advertising border connection information of an autonomous system, comprising:
establishing and maintaining (101), by a border node of the autonomous system, border connection information of the autonomous system, the border node of the autonomous system supporting Intermediate System to Intermediate System, ISIS, protocol, wherein the border connection information comprises an identifier of a neighbor border node of a neighbor autonomous system, Router_ID, and a number of the neighbor autonomous system, AS Number;
flooding (102), by the border node of the autonomous system, the border connection information within the autonomous system; and
receiving (103), by a node of the autonomous system, the border connection information,
wherein the process of flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises:
including the border connection information in a border connection description Sub-TLV field;
including the border connection description Sub-TLV field in a TLV field;
including the TLV field in a Link State Protocol Data Unit, LSP, message; and
flooding the LSP message.

The method of claim 1, wherein when border connection information is added on the border node, the process of flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises: determining (202, 203) whether the LSP message comprises a TLV field available for adding the border connection information;
if the LSP message comprises a TLV field available for adding the border connection information, including (204) the added border connection information in the border connection description Sub-TLV field in the TLV field, refreshing (206) the LSP message, and flooding (207) the refreshed LSP message; and
if the LSP message does not comprise a TLV field available for adding the border connection information, creating (205) a new TLV field, including the added border connection information in a border connection description Sub-TLV field in the new TLV field, refreshing (206) the LSP message, and flooding (207) the refreshed LSP message.

The method of claim 1, wherein when border connection information is deleted on the border node, the process of flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises:
determining (302) whether the LSP message comprises a border connection description Sub-TLV field that includes the border connection information to be deleted;

if the LSP message comprises the border connection description Sub-TLV field that includes the border connection information to be deleted, deleting (304) the corresponding border connection information in the border connection description Sub-TLV field, updating (304) the border connection description Sub-TLV field, refreshing (305) the LSP message, and flooding (306) the refreshed LSP message.

A method for advertising border connection information of an autonomous system, comprising:
establishing and maintaining (101), by a border node of the autonomous system, border connection information of the autonomous system, the border node of the autonomous system supporting Open Shortest Path First, OSPF, protocol, wherein the border connection information comprises an identifier of a neighbor border node of a neighbor autonomous system, Router_ID, and a number of the neighbor autonomous system, AS Number;
flooding (102), by the border node of the autonomous system, the border connection information within the autonomous system; and
receiving (103), by a node of the autonomous system, the border connection information,
wherein the process of flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises:
including the border connection information in a Link TLV field;
including the Link TLV field in a Link State Advertisement, LSA, message;
and

flooding the LSA message.

The method of claim 16, wherein when border connection information is added on the border node, the process of flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises: determining (602,) whether the LSA message comprises a Link TLV field available for adding the border connection information;
if the LSA message comprises a Link TLV field, adding (603) the border connection information in the Link TLV field, refreshing (605) the LSA message, and flooding (606) the refreshed LSA message; and
if the LSA message does not comprise a Link TLV field, creating (604) a new Link TLV field, including the added border connection information in the new Link TLV field, refreshing (605) the LSA message, and flooding (606) the refreshed LSA message.

The method of claim 16, wherein when border connection information is deleted on the border node, flooding the border connection information within the autonomous system comprises:
determining (702) whether the LSA message carries the border connection information to be deleted;

if the LSA message carries the border connection information to be deleted, deleting (704) the corresponding border connection information in the Link TLV field, refreshing (705) the LSA message, and flooding (706) the refreshed LSA message.

A border node for advertising border connection information of an autonomous system, comprising:
a border connection information collecting module, configured to obtain border connection information established by the border node, wherein the border connection information comprises an identifier of a neighbor border node of a neighbor autonomous system, Router_ID, and a number of the neighbor autonomous system, AS Number;
a border connection information database, configured to store border connection information of the autonomous system, the border connection information of the autonomous system comprising the border connection information established by the border node;
a message generating module, configured to package the border connection information established by the border node into a message; and
a message advertising module, configured to flood the message formed in the message generating module within the autonomous system,

wherein the border connection information is included in a border connection description Sub-TLV field, the border connection description Sub-TLV field being included in a TLV field in a Link State Protocol Data Unit, LSP, message if the border node of the autonomous system supports Intermediate System to Intermediate System, ISIS, protocol;

or

wherein the border connection information is included in a Link TLV field, the Link TLV field being included in a Link State Advertisement, LSA, message if the border node of the autonomous system supports Open Shortest Path First, OSPF, protocol.

The border node of claim 22, wherein the border node further comprises:
a message receiving module, configured to receive a message transmitted by other border node(s) within the autonomous system;
a message processing module, configured to parse the message received by the message receiving module, obtain border connection information of the autonomous system from the message, and store the obtained border connection information in the border connection information database.

Procédé selon la revendication 1, dans lequel, lorsque des informations de connexion de bordure sont supprimées du noeud de bordure, le processus de diffusion des informations de connexion de bordure au sein du système autonome comprend :
la détermination (302) du fait que le message LSP contient ou non un champ Sub-TLV de description de connexion de bordure qui inclut les informations de connexion de bordure à supprimer ;
si le message LSP comprend le champ Sub-TLV de description de connexion de bordure qui contient les informations de connexion de bordure à supprimer, la suppression (304) des informations de connexion de bordure correspondantes dans le champ Sub-TLV de description de connexion de bordure, la mise à jour (304) du champ Sub-TLV de description de connexion de bordure, le rafraichissement (305) du message LSP, et la diffusion (306) du message LSP rafraîchi.

Noeud de bordure destiné à annoncer des informations de connexion de bordure d'un système autonome, comprenant :
un module de collecte d'informations de connexion de bordure, configuré pour obtenir des informations de connexion de bordure établies par le noeud de bordure,
les informations de connexion de bordure comprenant un identifiant d'un noeud de bordure voisin d'un système autonome voisin, Router_ID, et un numéro du système autonome voisin, Numéro AS ;
une base de données d'informations de connexion de bordure, configurée pour stocker des informations de connexion de bordure du système autonome, les informations de connexion de bordure du système autonome comprenant les informations de connexion de bordure établies par le noeud de bordure ;
un module générateur de message, configuré pour empaqueter les informations de connexion de bordure établies par le noeud de bordure dans un message ; et
un module d'annonce de message, configuré pour diffuser le message formé dans le module générateur de message au sein du système autonome,
dans lequel les informations de connexion de bordure sont incluses dans un champ Sub-TLV de description de connexion de bordure, le champ Sub-TLV de description de connexion de bordure étant inclus dans un champ TLV, dans un message d'Unité de Données de Protocole d'État de Liaison, LSP, si le noeud de bordure du système autonome prend en charge un protocole de Système Intermédiaire à Système Intermédiaire, ISIS ;
ou dans lequel les informations de connexion de bordure sont incluses dans un champ TLV de Liaison, le champ TLV de Liaison étant inclus dans un message d'Annonce d'État de Liaison, LSA, si le noeud de bordure du système autonome prend en charge un protocole du type Trajet le plus Court Ouvert en Premier, OSPF.

Noeud de bordure selon la revendication 22, dans lequel le noeud de bordure comprend en outre :
un module de réception de message, configuré pour recevoir un message transmis par un autre ou d'autres noeud(s) de bordure au sein du système autonome ;
un module de traitement de message, configuré pour analyser le message reçu par le module de réception de message, obtenir des informations de connexion de bordure du système autonome à partir du message, et stocker les informations de connexion de bordure obtenues dans la base de données d'informations de connexion de bordure.
